      "different": "The EU pairs rights with observable audit, extraterritorial reach, portable cloud, multi-provider sourcing, and allocated derived rights, while the UK relies on declared control, domestic reach, preferred partners, single-provider sourcing, and unallocated downstream rights.",
      "impact": "This matters because the EU model makes rights operational across systems and borders, while the UK model risks protecting inputs without controlling the infrastructure and derived value layer."
